author: National Geographic
description:
The warm, shallow waters of the Gulf of Mexico are a thriving hub of industry and commerce, but they’re also rocket fuel for hurricanes. The Gulf Coast has been decimated in the past, but every time the marine and coastal economies bounce back. With more people, more ships, more fishermen and more oil platforms here than ever before, three major storms will bring a new level of devastation. 

Gathering Storm | S1, E2

author: National Geographic
description:
Emerging in California during the Cold War, the Renaissance Pleasure Faire gave blacklisted creatives a stage to perform and reimagine life in the 16th century—complete with actors cosplaying historical figures, and drawing inspiration from the commedia dell'arte and Elizabethan fairs. Now popular across the U.S., Halley Brown reveals more about the origins of these events and how political history led to their development.
